linist state, this powerful work encompasses the dictator’s brutal reign from his achievement of total power in 1929 to his death in 1953.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDictatorshipzSoviet Union. 0aTotalitarianismxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / Russia & the Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh1 aGilbert, Steven, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKomljen, Ivo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaber, Samantha Jeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831106677140 cprintz978030013698240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300220575423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300220575/original  a978-3-11-066771-4  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles